Examination Hall Seat Allocation System
Course: UCS310 – Database Management Systems | Thapar Institute

Team: Vivek Pandey, Anant Agrawal, Gulnaz

🚀 The Hook: One-Click Automation
Manually assigning seats to hundreds of students across multiple exam halls is a chaotic, error-prone nightmare. This system completely automates it.

Add students, register them for a course, and click one button. The system instantly and randomly distributes every student across available halls, assigns unique seat numbers, and generates a complete seating plan.

The best part? The database enforces the rules. No two students share a seat, no hall gets overbooked, and every single allocation is strictly traceable.

🛠️ Tech Stack
Frontend: HTML, CSS, Vanilla JS, Chart.js (Visual Analytics)

Backend: Node.js, Express.js (REST API)

Database: MySQL 8.0

🧠 The Engine: Core Database Architecture
This project isn't just a basic CRUD app; it relies on heavy database-level logic to ensure data integrity.

The Watchdog Trigger (hall_capacity_trg): Fires BEFORE INSERT on the Allocation table. It calculates current hall occupancy and strictly blocks any insert if the hall has reached its limit. The frontend literally cannot overbook a room.

The Brain Procedure (allocate_random_seats): This stored procedure handles the heavy lifting. It verifies global capacity, opens a cursor to fetch enrolled students randomly, and loops through to assign halls and seats.

Collision & Transaction Handling: If a random seat is already taken, a UNIQUE constraint catches it, and the procedure auto-retries. It only COMMITS upon 100% success and completely ROLLBACKS if a single allocation fails.

Bulletproof Constraints:

UNIQUE(exam_id, student_id): One seat per student, guaranteed.

UNIQUE(exam_id, hall_id, seat_no): No sharing seats, ever.

AUTO_INCREMENT: Handles ID generation cleanly (acting as our Oracle Sequence equivalent).

🖥️ Live Features
Seat Allocation Engine: Watch the stored procedure execute and assign seats in real-time.

Live Dashboards: Add students, manage hall capacities, and enroll students into courses instantly.

Visual Analytics: Real-time Chart.js doughnut graphs displaying student distribution and hall occupancy post-allocation.

Seating Plan Generation: Instantly outputs a full, hall-wise breakdown of every student.
